  "text": "## CronJob v1beta1 to batch/v1 Migration\n\nThe Kubernetes CronJob API has been migrated from `batch/v1beta1` to `batch/v1`, with both versions coexisting in kubernetes/kubernetes v1.32.0. Here are the key findings:\n\n### API Type Definitions\n\nBoth `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1/types.go` and `staging/src/k8s.io/api/batch/v1beta1/types.go` define the CronJob and CronJobSpec types. The key difference is the **TimeZone field** at line 748 in v1/types.go and line 99 in v1beta1/types.go:\n\n```go\nTimeZone *string `json:\"timeZone,omitempty\" protobuf:\"bytes,8,opt,name=timeZone\"`\n```\n\nThis field is optional and allows specifying the time zone for cron schedule execution. The internal batch API definition is in `pkg/apis/batch/types.go` (lines 650-766), which serves as the internal representation that both v1 and v1beta1 convert to/from.\n\n### Conversion Functions\n\nThe conversion between `v1`, `v1beta1`, and the internal `batch` types is handled through auto-generated conversion functions in:\n\n- `pkg/apis/batch/v1/zz_generated.conversion.go`: Contains conversion functions like `Convert_v1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob`, `autoConvert_v1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob`, `Convert_batch_CronJob_To_v1_CronJob`, and the corresponding `CronJobSpec` conversion functions.\n\n- `pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/zz_generated.conversion.go`: Contains parallel conversion functions for v1beta1, such as `Convert_v1beta1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob`, `autoConvert_v1beta1_CronJob_To_batch_CronJob`, and their spec equivalents.\n\nThe conversion functions handle conversion of all CronJobSpec fields including Schedule, TimeZone, StartingDeadlineSeconds, ConcurrencyPolicy, Suspend, JobTemplate, SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit, and FailedJobsHistoryLimit.\n\n### Custom Conversion Setup\n\n- `pkg/apis/batch/v1/conversion.go`: Sets up field label conversions for Job, JobTemplate, and CronJob. Also provides wrapper functions for JobSpec conversion.\n\n- `pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/conversion.go`: Defines field label conversion functions supporting metadata.name, metadata.namespace, and status.successful labels for CronJob, Job, and JobTemplate.\n\n### Defaulting Logic\n\n**v1 Defaulting** (`pkg/apis/batch/v1/defaults.go`, lines 87-100):\n- Sets ConcurrencyPolicy to `AllowConcurrent` if empty\n- Sets Suspend to `false` if nil\n- Sets SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit to `3` if nil (using `ptr.To[int32](3)`)\n- Sets FailedJobsHistoryLimit to `1` if nil (using `ptr.To[int32](1)`)\n\n**v1beta1 Defaulting** (`pkg/apis/batch/v1beta1/defaults.go`, lines 28-43):\n- Sets ConcurrencyPolicy to `AllowConcurrent` if empty\n- Sets Suspend to a new bool if nil\n- Sets SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit to 3 via manual pointer allocation\n- Sets FailedJobsHistoryLimit to 1 via manual pointer allocation\n\nThe key difference is that v1 uses the modern `ptr.To()` utility while v1beta1 uses manual pointer allocation. Generated defaults are in `zz_generated.defaults.go` files for both versions, with `SetObjectDefaults_CronJob` also calling `SetDefaults_PodSpec` on the job template.\n\n### Validation\n\n`pkg/apis/batch/validation/validation.go` implements critical validation logic:\n\n**ValidateCronJobCreate** (line 715): Validates CronJob on creation, checking metadata and calling `validateCronJobSpec`.\n\n**ValidateCronJobUpdate** (line 730): Validates CronJob updates, comparing old and new specs and calling `validateCronJobSpec`.\n\n**validateCronJobSpec** (line 740): Core validation that checks the spec, including schedule validation and TimeZone handling.\n\n**validateTimeZone** (line 816): Validates the TimeZone field by:\n1. Checking for empty string if provided (line 822)\n2. Validating component names using regex pattern `^[A-Za-z\\.\\-_0-9+]{1,14}$` (line 814)\n3. Rejecting 'LOCAL' timezone (line 834)\n4. Attempting to load timezone with `time.LoadLocation()` (line 838)\n\nCrucially, `validateCronJobSpec` also checks for deprecated TZ or CRON_TZ environment variables in the schedule string (line 800), enforcing that users must use the timeZone field instead.\n\n### Registry and Storage\n\n`pkg/registry/batch/cronjob/strategy.go` implements the `cronJobStrategy` type with:\n- **Validate** method (line 112): Calls `batchvalidation.ValidateCronJobCreate`\n- **ValidateUpdate** method (line 143): Calls `batchvalidation.ValidateCronJobUpdate`\n- **GetResetFields** method (line 73): Returns immutable fields (status) for both batch/v1 and batch/v1beta1\n- **PrepareForUpdate** method (line 97): Clears status on update and handles pod spec field dropping\n\n`pkg/registry/batch/cronjob/storage/storage.go` provides REST endpoints for CronJob CRUD operations using the defined strategy.\n\n### Installation and Scheme Registration\n\n`pkg/apis/batch/install/install.go` registers both batch/v1 and batch/v1beta1 with the scheme, setting v1 as the preferred version via `scheme.SetVersionPriority(v1.SchemeGroupVersion, v1beta1.SchemeGroupVersion)` (line 39).\n\n### Key Differences Between Versions\n\n1. **Deprecation Status**: v1beta1 is marked as deprecated (introduced in 1.8, deprecated in 1.21, removed in 1.25 prerelease lifecycle annotations)\n2. **Pointer Utilities**: v1 uses modern `ptr.To()` utility functions; v1beta1 uses manual pointer allocation\n3. **TimeZone Field**: Both versions support TimeZone as an optional field to replace deprecated TZ/CRON_TZ environment variables\n4. **Default Values**: Both use identical default values (ConcurrencyPolicy=Allow, Suspend=false, SuccessfulJobsHistoryLimit=3, FailedJobsHistoryLimit=1)\n5. **Field Label Conversions**: Both versions implement field label conversions for metadata.name, metadata.namespace, and status.successful"
